Print the location in memory of a data frame

Source: R/deprec-location.R
location.Rd

This is useful for understand how and when dplyr makes copies of data frames

location(df)

changes(x, y)

Arguments

df

a data frame
x, y

two data frames to compare

Examples

location(mtcars)

#> Warning: `location()` was deprecated in dplyr 1.0.0.
#> Please use `lobst::ref()` instead.
#> <0x7fcfd301aab8>
#> Variables:
#>  * mpg:       <0x7fcfcb4f0cc0>
#>  * cyl:       <0x7fcfcb4b5ac0>

#>  * hp:        <0x7fcfd3b08bf0>
#>  * drat:      <0x7fcfcb481910>
#>  * wt:        <0x7fcfd3b53bf0>
#>  * qsec:      <0x7fcfd3b4a0d0>
